## What I built

A complete, runnable Node.js/Express integration hub:

**Core functionality**
- **Accounts** — register/login/logout, bcrypt-hashed passwords (cost 12).
- **Inbound webhooks** — each gets a unique secret URL `/in/<token>`; events are stored.
- **Outbound actions** — per-webhook target URLs (POST/PUT/PATCH/GET) that the hub calls when an event arrives.
- **Dashboard** — recent events + deliveries with HTTP status/error and a one-click **Retry**.
- **Storage** — SQLite (`better-sqlite3`), all access via parameterised prepared statements.

**Files**
- `package.json`, `.env.example`, `README.md`, `.gitignore`
- `src/`: `app.js`, `server.js`, `config.js`, `db.js`; `middleware/` (auth, csrf, errors); `lib/` (ssrf, delivery, validate); `services/dispatcher.js`; `routes/` (auth, webhooks, dashboard, inbound); `views/` (EJS, auto-escaped); `public/styles.css`

**Security controls mapped to your requirements**
- SQLi → prepared statements everywhere · Passwords → bcrypt+salt · XSS → EJS auto-escaping + strict CSP forbidding inline scripts/styles · CSRF → per-session synchroniser token (constant-time compare; inbound ingress exempt as token-authed M2M) · IDOR → every query scoped by session `user_id` · Cookies → `HttpOnly`/`SameSite=Lax`/`Secure` (when `COOKIE_SECURE=true`), session id regenerated on login · Headers → Helmet · Errors → central handler logs server-side, returns generic messages · Secrets → env only (fails closed in production if `SESSION_SECRET` missing) · Rate limiting on app + ingress.
- **SSRF** → scheme allow-list (http/https), credentials rejected, and host validation performed *inside the socket DNS lookup* (defeats DNS rebinding) blocking private/loopback/link-local/CGNAT/reserved ranges incl. `169.254.169.254`, `::1`, `fc00::/7`; IPv4-mapped IPv6 unwrapped; connection/read timeouts; max response size; redirects not followed.

